Motion Typography
My initial work on After Effects and Illustrator to create a motion typography film for a course which I re-created to publish on my Instagram by changing dimensions. This was a two week course work and two additional week for the edit.
Tool and Techniques
Sketching out the sketches on Procreate is something that came handy to me when bringing all the illustartion together on After Effects. I sketch out the details and then approve designs before carving them on Illustrator.
Design Process:
Step 1: Created rough sketches of elements along with transitions on procreate.
Step 2: Created a color profile to harmonize text and elements. Choose fonts pairing working well with the elements and motion.
Step 3: Illustrated elements and set it up in different layers on Adobe Illustrator to scale.
Step 4: Created scenes with illustrations on After Effects.
Step 5: Once, everything was ready, I added animation to text and elements.
Challenges and design solutions:
1. Initial use of only cursive font gave static and rhythmic results. Solution: Added more paired fonts for dynamism.
2. Chorus contained a lot of elements pulling attention from the texts.
Solution: Used texts to symbolize the elements
Learning Outcomes
1. Understanding the difference between motion typography and lyric video.
2. Acquiring tips and tricks through online sources.
